    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term referring to any of the larger species of marine mammals of the order Cetacea that have fore-limbs like fins and a tail with horizontal flukes, and are hunted for their oil and whalebone.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
